
## Joe Durso

Joseph P. Durso (June 22, 1924 â€“ December 31, 2004) was an American sportswriter for The New York Times from 1950 until his death, most noted for his coverage of baseball. Born in New York City, he was awarded the J. G. Taylor Spink Award in 1995.

